  "original_title": "Ali Sabry, Wijeyadasa to head to UNHRC today (5)",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Ali Sabry, Wijeyadasa to head to UNHRC today (5)",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "COLOMBO (News 1st); A delegation headed by Minister of Foreign Affairs President's Counsel Ali Sabry will head to Geneva today (5) to attend the 51st session of the United Nations Human Rights Council sessions (UNHRC).",
        "The delegation includes Minister of Justice President's Counsel51st\u00a0 Wijayadasa Rajapaksa, and officials from the Attorney General's Department and the Foreign Ministry.",
        "The 51st session of the Human Rights Council sessions is due to begin on the 12th of September.",
        "Foreign Minister Ali Sabry has said the intervention of external parties in domestic matters of Sri Lanka will be rejected at the sessions.",
        "The Minister added that solutions to the internal issues in Sri Lanka will be found through a domestic mechanism.",
        "The Minister is due to address the 51st session of the Human Rights Council on the 12th.",
        "Public Finance Committee Chief Harsha demands President publicize IMF conditions"
      ],
